1 independent contractor basis with any licensed
2 security agency as defined in this section or any
3 private business or person to perform security or
4 investigative services,
5 c.
6 d. any person whose terms of employment as a security
7 guard are governed by a collective bargaining
8 agreement on May 9, 1989, and
9 d.
10 e. any person who is employed as a full-time security
11 guard by a financial institution on May 9, 1989;
12 8. "Armed security guard" means a security guard authorized to
13 carry a firearm;
14 9. "Investigative agency" means a self-employed private
15 investigator, a firm, a corporation, or other private legal entity
16 in the business of soliciting the business of private investigation
17 and/or providing private investigations and investigators;
18 10. "Special event" means a public activity in the form of an
19 athletic contest, charity event, exposition or similar event that
20 occurs only on an annual or noncontinuing basis; and
21 11. "Special event license" means a temporary license issued
22 pursuant to the Oklahoma Security Guard and Private Investigator Act
23 which restricts the license holder to employment as a security guard
24 only for the duration of a particular event.
